# UI Component Refinement Workflow
# Refines multiple UI components in parallel using specialized temp agents
# Each component gets its own agent for parallel processing

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# PHASE 1: Discovery - Identify Components to Refine
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

general-purpose:"Analyze the project and user requirements to identify which UI components need refinement.

For EACH component identified, provide:
- Component name (e.g., 'Button', 'Card', 'Modal')
- Current location (file path)
- Current styling issues (what's wrong)
- Desired aesthetic (what we want to achieve)
- Framework/library used (React, Vue, Tailwind, CSS Modules, etc.)
- Any constraints (brand colors, accessibility requirements)

Output as a structured list of components with all details.

Ask user to confirm the list and add/remove components as needed.":components_identified ->

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# PHASE 2: Parallel Refinement - Each Component Gets Its Own Agent
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Define temp agents for component-specific refinement
# Each agent is responsible for the COMPLETE refinement workflow of ONE component

@define-agents {
  component-refiner-1: {
    base: "general-purpose",
    prompt: "UI/UX specialist focused on component design. You will refine ONE specific component through: design inspiration research, design proposal creation, implementation, and quality verification. Maintain component functionality while improving visual design. Ensure responsive design and accessibility (ARIA, contrast ratios). Provide file:line references for all changes.",
    model: "sonnet"
  },

  component-refiner-2: {
    base: "general-purpose",
    prompt: "UI/UX specialist focused on component design. You will refine ONE specific component through: design inspiration research, design proposal creation, implementation, and quality verification. Maintain component functionality while improving visual design. Ensure responsive design and accessibility (ARIA, contrast ratios). Provide file:line references for all changes.",
    model: "sonnet"
  },

  component-refiner-3: {
    base: "general-purpose",
    prompt: "UI/UX specialist focused on component design. You will refine ONE specific component through: design inspiration research, design proposal creation, implementation, and quality verification. Maintain component functionality while improving visual design. Ensure responsive design and accessibility (ARIA, contrast ratios). Provide file:line references for all changes.",
    model: "sonnet"
  },

  component-refiner-4: {
    base: "general-purpose",
    prompt: "UI/UX specialist focused on component design. You will refine ONE specific component through: design inspiration research, design proposal creation, implementation, and quality verification. Maintain component functionality while improving visual design. Ensure responsive design and accessibility (ARIA, contrast ratios). Provide file:line references for all changes.",
    model: "sonnet"
  },

  component-refiner-5: {
    base: "general-purpose",
    prompt: "UI/UX specialist focused on component design. You will refine ONE specific component through: design inspiration research, design proposal creation, implementation, and quality verification. Maintain component functionality while improving visual design. Ensure responsive design and accessibility (ARIA, contrast ratios). Provide file:line references for all changes.",
    model: "sonnet"
  }
}

# Run refinement agents in parallel - each handles one component
# NOTE: Only the agents for identified components will be used
# If user has 2 components, only refiner-1 and refiner-2 will execute

[
  $component-refiner-1:"You are assigned to component: [FIRST COMPONENT from {components_identified}]

**STEP 1: Design Inspiration Research**
Search Dribbble, Pinterest, and design galleries for inspiration specific to this component type.
Find 5-8 examples with modern, professional styling.
Document: key design elements (colors, spacing, typography, animations), what makes each example special, source links.

**STEP 2: Design Proposal**
Based on inspirations and user requirements, create detailed design specification for THIS component:
- Color palette (hex codes)
- Spacing values (margin, padding)
- Typography (fonts, sizes, weights)
- Border radius, shadows, transitions
- Specific CSS/styling values that match inspiration
- How it fits with other components in the design system

**STEP 3: Implementation**
Implement the design proposal:
- Update component file using project's styling approach (CSS modules, Tailwind, styled-components, etc.)
- Maintain ALL existing functionality
- Apply new visual design
- Ensure responsive design (mobile, tablet, desktop)
- Ensure accessibility (ARIA labels, keyboard navigation, contrast ratios)
- Add comments explaining major design decisions

**STEP 4: Quality Verification**
Review your implementation:
- Styling is consistent with design proposal
- Code is clean and maintainable
- Accessibility standards met (WCAG AA minimum)
- Responsive on different screen sizes
- No breaking changes to functionality
- Component integrates well with design system

**OUTPUT:**
Provide comprehensive report:
- Component name and file path
- Design inspirations used (with links)
- Design specification applied
- Code changes made (file:line references)
- Before/after visual description
- Verification checklist completed":component_1_refined ||

  $component-refiner-2:"You are assigned to component: [SECOND COMPONENT from {components_identified}]

[Same instructions as component-refiner-1 but for the second component]":component_2_refined ||

  $component-refiner-3:"You are assigned to component: [THIRD COMPONENT from {components_identified}]

[Same instructions as component-refiner-1 but for the third component]":component_3_refined ||

  $component-refiner-4:"You are assigned to component: [FOURTH COMPONENT from {components_identified}]

[Same instructions as component-refiner-1 but for the fourth component]":component_4_refined ||

  $component-refiner-5:"You are assigned to component: [FIFTH COMPONENT from {components_identified}]

[Same instructions as component-refiner-1 but for the fifth component]":component_5_refined
] ->

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# PHASE 3: Aggregation - Consolidate All Results
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

general-purpose:"Aggregate refinement results from all components:

From: {component_1_refined}, {component_2_refined}, {component_3_refined}, {component_4_refined}, {component_5_refined}

Create comprehensive summary:
- List all components refined
- Design elements implemented per component
- All files modified (with file:line references)
- Before/after comparisons for each component
- Consistency check: do all components work together as a cohesive design system?
- Any issues or warnings

Present results to user for review.":aggregated_results ->

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# PHASE 4: User Review Checkpoint
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

@review-all-components:"
## Component Refinement Results

{aggregated_results}

**Review all components above.**

Options:
- **Accept all** - All components look good, finalize the work
- **Request changes** - Specify which components need adjustments and what changes
- **Reject specific components** - Identify which components to revert or re-do

What would you like to do?
":user_feedback ->

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# PHASE 5: Handle Feedback (Conditional)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

general-purpose:"Analyze user feedback: {user_feedback}

If user accepted all components:
- Set status: APPROVED
- Prepare finalization

If user requested changes:
- Identify which specific components need changes
- Document what changes are needed for each
- Set status: NEEDS_REFINEMENT
- List components and their required changes

If user rejected specific components:
- Identify which components to revert
- Set status: NEEDS_REWORK
- Document what to do with each component

Output structured decision with next steps.":feedback_processed ->

# Conditional: If refinements are needed, create re-refinement tasks
(if needs-refinement)~> general-purpose:"Based on {feedback_processed}, apply the requested changes to specific components:

For each component that needs changes:
1. Review what changes were requested
2. Apply those specific changes to the component
3. Verify the changes meet user expectations
4. Document what was changed

Provide updated report for modified components.":changes_applied ->

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# PHASE 6: Finalization
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

general-purpose:"Create final summary of UI refinement work:

**Components Refined:**
List all components with their file paths

**Design Elements Implemented:**
Summarize the design system updates made

**Files Modified:**
Complete list of all modified files with brief description of changes

**Before/After Comparison:**
High-level summary of visual improvements

**Next Steps:**
Suggest:
- Testing the components in the application
- Updating design system documentation
- Creating git commit with message: 'style: refine UI components - [component names]'
- Sharing the changes with the team

Provide git commit command with all modified files.":refinement_complete ->

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# PHASE 7: Completion
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

@workflow-complete:"
## UI Refinement Complete

{refinement_complete}

All components have been refined and are ready for testing.
"

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# NOTES
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# This workflow handles 1-5 components in a single run.
# Unused agents (e.g., if only 2 components) will simply not execute.
# Each component is processed in PARALLEL for maximum efficiency.
# User reviews ALL components at once rather than one-by-one.
# If > 5 components needed, run workflow multiple times or extend agent definitions.
